This paper deals with reinforcement learning methods for continuous control problems, which are typically studied in the machine learning subfield of reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific applications mentioned in the abstract, robotics control (cs.RO) and real-time strategy games, are also relevant subfields. The paper also discusses variance reduction techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and control systems (cs.SY).
